<br>
Fact 1:<br>
<br>
The collision occurred in International airspace.<br>
<br>
The US EP-3 Aries II aircraft and the two Chinese F-8 (Mig-21) aircraft had every right to be there. International law recognizes ever countries borders to extend 12 miles into the ocean. The accident occurred over 60 miles from Chinese soil.<br>
<br>
Fact 2:<br>
<br>
The EP-3 Aries II is not a “Spy” plane.<br>
<br>
The EP-3 is in fact a reconnaissance aircraft. It is slow, un-maneuverable and projects a huge radar silhouette. The fact that the EP-3 was there was a secret to no one. EP-3s’ are used because they are a trusted airframe and have very long legs. The fact is, world powers monitor each other’s activities continually. In fact, the Chinese monitor US message traffic through the use of technically equipped fishing trawlers. <br>
<br>
Fact 3:<br>
<br>
The EP-3 did not “Ram” the F-8.<br>
<br>
This statement is insane. EP-3 max speed: 482 Mph, F-8 Max speed: 1700 Mph. It would be virtually impossible for an EP-3 to ram a highly maneuverable interceptor like an F-8 unless the Chinese pilot had control problems or was incredibly inept. Here’s an easy way to try this for your self. Go hop in a rowboat and try to “Ram” a jet powered Ski boat. <br>
<br>
In addition, at the time of the incident the American EP-3 was on cruise control for God’s sake!<br>
<br>
Fact 4:<br>
<br>
The US EP-3 did enter Chinese airspace after the collision.<br>
<br>
It was broadcasting Mayday mayday mayday because it had sustained sever damage after being hit in an air-to-air collision from the Chinese interceptor. In fact it broadcast the international mayday signal over 45 times with no response from the Chinese. The Chinese military consciously chose to ignore a mayday signal from a disabled aircraft.<br>
<br>
Fact 5:<br>
<br>
The Chinese military is full of crap.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
